<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Note: The &#96;uwtable&#39; attribute is about the ABI or the user mandating an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// entry in the unwind table. The &#96;nounwind&#39; attribute is about an exception</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// In a theoretical system that uses tables for profiling and SjLj for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// exceptions, they would be fully independent. In a normal system that uses</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="78"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// tables for both, the semantics are:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="79"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="80"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// nil                = Needs an entry because an exception might pass by.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="81"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// nounwind           = No need for an entry</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="82"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// uwtable            = Needs an entry because the ABI says so and because</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="83"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///                      an exception might pass by.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="84"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// uwtable + nounwind = Needs an entry because the ABI says so.</span></CodeLine>
